<subSubSection id="C34803C0DC7F1A7296E2B16B8C70A109" pageId="26" pageNumber="199" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BED504BDC7F1A7296E2B16B88CFA229" blockId="26.[189,457,264,290]" box="[189,457,264,290]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">
<heading id="D0A5E727DC7F1A7296E2B16B88CFA229" bold="true" box="[189,457,264,290]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="26" pageNumber="199" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9268C59DC7F1A7296E2B16B88CFA229" bold="true" box="[189,457,264,290]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED504BDC7F1A7296E2B1548C70A109" blockId="26.[188,1400,311,514]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C522BC8DC7F1A72971BB1548B26A25A" authority="Nolasco &amp; Valdez-Mondragón, 2022" authorityName="Nolasco &amp; Valdez-Mondragón" authorityYear="2022" box="[324,544,311,337]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Physocyclus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="26" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lyncis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9268C59DC7F1A72971BB1548B26A25A" box="[324,544,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Physocyclus lyncis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2153122DC7F1A729478B15B8B84A259" box="[551,642,312,338]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resemble 
<taxonomicName id="4C522BC8DC7F1A7294A7B15B8AA6A25A" authorityName="Chamberlin &amp; Gertsch" authorityYear="1929" box="[760,928,311,337]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Physocyclus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="26" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="californicus">
<emphasis id="B9268C59DC7F1A7294A7B15B8AA6A25A" box="[760,928,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">P. californicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by shape of epigynum, with semisquare shape in anterior part; VAE with a flat, wide shape in frontal and lateral views (
<figureCitation id="13694CCEDC7F1A72921BB1398D9CA27F" box="[1092,1178,346,372]" captionStart="Figs 58–63" captionStartId="25.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,613,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-70@25.[189,1398,610,1869]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 58–63. Physocyclus lyncis sp. nov. Female (holotype). 58–60. Habitus in dorsal, lateral and ventral views, respectively. 61–63. Epigynum in ventral, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. Scale bars: 58– 60 = 1 mm; 61–63 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484139/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
; VM 2010: figs 12, 14). In 
<taxonomicName id="4C522BC8DC7F1A729750B11D8868A29C" authority="Nolasco &amp; Valdez-Mondragón, 2022" authorityName="Nolasco &amp; Valdez-Mondragón" authorityYear="2022" box="[271,366,381,407]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Physocyclus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="26" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lyncis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9268C59DC7F1A729750B11D8868A29C" box="[271,366,381,407]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">P. lyncis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2153122DC7F1A729729B11D88C9A293" box="[374,463,382,408]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(1) VAE long, wide, almost flat, ending in rounded tip, with dark region between them (
<figureCitation id="13694CCEDC7F1A729757B1C28895A2B0" box="[264,403,416,443]" captionStart="Figs 58–63" captionStartId="25.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,613,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-70@25.[189,1398,610,1869]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 58–63. Physocyclus lyncis sp. nov. Female (holotype). 58–60. Habitus in dorsal, lateral and ventral views, respectively. 61–63. Epigynum in ventral, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. Scale bars: 58– 60 = 1 mm; 61–63 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484139/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Figs 61–62</figureCitation>
); (2) VAE closer to each other; (3) PP long, elongated, slightly curved (
<figureCitation id="13694CCEDC7F1A7292BAB1C28C38A2B0" box="[1253,1342,416,443]" captionStart="Figs 58–63" captionStartId="25.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,613,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-70@25.[189,1398,610,1869]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 58–63. Physocyclus lyncis sp. nov. Female (holotype). 58–60. Habitus in dorsal, lateral and ventral views, respectively. 61–63. Epigynum in ventral, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. Scale bars: 58– 60 = 1 mm; 61–63 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484139/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
); (4) sclerotized arc of uterus pointing toward right side; (5) body coloration light beige, with a light brown inverted triangle pattern in carapace (
<figureCitation id="13694CCEDC7F1A729430B1848BC3A109" box="[623,709,487,514]" captionStart="Figs 58–63" captionStartId="25.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,613,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-70@25.[189,1398,610,1869]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 58–63. Physocyclus lyncis sp. nov. Female (holotype). 58–60. Habitus in dorsal, lateral and ventral views, respectively. 61–63. Epigynum in ventral, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. Scale bars: 58– 60 = 1 mm; 61–63 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484139/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
); (6) irregular pale gray marks spread on sternum (
<figureCitation id="13694CCEDC7F1A72934DB1848C6FA109" box="[1298,1385,487,514]" captionStart="Figs 58–63" captionStartId="25.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,613,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-70@25.[189,1398,610,1869]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 58–63. Physocyclus lyncis sp. nov. Female (holotype). 58–60. Habitus in dorsal, lateral and ventral views, respectively. 61–63. Epigynum in ventral, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. Scale bars: 58– 60 = 1 mm; 61–63 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484139/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34803C0DC7F1A7296E2B24A8D02A19F" pageId="26" pageNumber="199" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BED504BDC7F1A7296E2B24A8842A148" blockId="26.[189,324,553,579]" box="[189,324,553,579]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">
<heading id="D0A5E727DC7F1A7296E2B24A8842A148" bold="true" box="[189,324,553,579]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="26" pageNumber="199" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9268C59DC7F1A7296E2B24A8842A148" bold="true" box="[189,324,553,579]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED504BDC7F1A7296E2B2348D02A19F" blockId="26.[188,1399,599,661]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">
The species name is a noun in apposition and refers to the 
<typeStatus id="54E9EEE9DC7F1A72953BB23B8A91A179" box="[868,919,600,626]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">type</typeStatus>
locality where the species was collected: Cueva del Lince, Ejido La Primavera, Ecotourist Park, 
<collectingRegion id="49969EA9DC7F1A72951BB2198A91A19F" box="[836,919,634,660]" country="Mexico" name="Jalisco" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Jalisco</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F34510DBDC7F1A7295FCB2198D06A19F" box="[931,1024,634,660]" name="Mexico" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Mexico</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
