<paragraph id="8BED504BDC7F1A7296E2B4C68848A7B4" blockId="26.[189,334,1189,1215]" box="[189,334,1189,1215]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">
<heading id="D0A5E727DC7F1A7296E2B4C68848A7B4" bold="true" box="[189,334,1189,1215]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="26" pageNumber="199" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9268C59DC7F1A7296E2B4C68848A7B4" bold="true" box="[189,334,1189,1215]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED504BDC7F1A7296B5B4B78B88A7E5" blockId="26.[189,1398,1235,1368]" box="[234,654,1235,1262]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis id="B9268C59DC7F1A7296B5B4B78843A7E5" bold="true" box="[234,325,1236,1262]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="54E9EEE9DC7F1A72970AB4B088C6A7E6" box="[341,448,1235,1261]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">holotype</typeStatus>
, CNAN-T01476)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED504BDC7F1A7296E2B4948BB1A65C" blockId="26.[189,1398,1235,1368]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">MEASUREMENTS. Total length: 4.5. Carapace 1.6 long, 1.9 wide. Clypeus 0.5. Diameter AME 0.10, ALE 0.12, PME 0.12, PLE 0.15. Distance ALE-PME 0.11, PME-PME 0.18. Leg lengths: I missing; tibia II: missing; tibia III: 4.8; tibia IV: 6.4.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED504BDC7F1A7296E2B51C882AA52D" blockId="26.[189,1401,1406,1574]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">
PROSOMA. Carapace light beige with light brown irregular pattern, triangular-shaped around fovea and posterior part of ocular region (
<figureCitation id="13694CCEDC7F1A729472B5C18B82A6B7" box="[557,644,1441,1468]" captionStart="Figs 58–63" captionStartId="25.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,613,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-70@25.[189,1398,610,1869]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 58–63. Physocyclus lyncis sp. nov. Female (holotype). 58–60. Habitus in dorsal, lateral and ventral views, respectively. 61–63. Epigynum in ventral, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. Scale bars: 58– 60 = 1 mm; 61–63 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484139/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
). Fovea longitudinal. Clypeus entirely light gray, without marks. Chelicerae light gray, without stridulatory files (
<figureCitation id="13694CCEDC7F1A729556B5A68A63A6EB" box="[777,869,1477,1504]" captionStart="Figs 58–63" captionStartId="25.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,613,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-70@25.[189,1398,610,1869]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 58–63. Physocyclus lyncis sp. nov. Female (holotype). 58–60. Habitus in dorsal, lateral and ventral views, respectively. 61–63. Epigynum in ventral, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. Scale bars: 58– 60 = 1 mm; 61–63 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484139/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
). Sternum with light beige coloration, with spread and irregular pale gray spots. Endites and labium longer than wide, with light brown coloration (
<figureCitation id="13694CCEDC7F1A729699B6688818A52D" box="[198,286,1547,1574]" captionStart="Figs 58–63" captionStartId="25.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,613,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-70@25.[189,1398,610,1869]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 58–63. Physocyclus lyncis sp. nov. Female (holotype). 58–60. Habitus in dorsal, lateral and ventral views, respectively. 61–63. Epigynum in ventral, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. Scale bars: 58– 60 = 1 mm; 61–63 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484139/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED504BDC7F1A7296E2B62E8BCDA580" blockId="26.[189,1399,1613,1675]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">
LEGS. All segments with same coloration as carapace. Tibiae and femora with light gray rings distally. Trochanter light gray retrolaterally (
<figureCitation id="13694CCEDC7F1A72943AB6138BBBA580" box="[613,701,1648,1675]" captionStart="Figs 58–63" captionStartId="25.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,613,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-70@25.[189,1398,610,1869]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 58–63. Physocyclus lyncis sp. nov. Female (holotype). 58–60. Habitus in dorsal, lateral and ventral views, respectively. 61–63. Epigynum in ventral, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. Scale bars: 58– 60 = 1 mm; 61–63 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484139/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED504BDC7F1A7296E2B6D288BCA5E4" blockId="26.[189,1399,1713,1775]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">
OPISTHOSOMA. Globose, longer than wide, with big dark marks, gray and white (
<figureCitation id="13694CCEDC7F1A729201B6D28DE1A5C7" box="[1118,1255,1713,1740]" captionStart="Figs 58–63" captionStartId="25.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,613,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-70@25.[189,1398,610,1869]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 58–63. Physocyclus lyncis sp. nov. Female (holotype). 58–60. Habitus in dorsal, lateral and ventral views, respectively. 61–63. Epigynum in ventral, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. Scale bars: 58– 60 = 1 mm; 61–63 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484139/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Figs 58–59</figureCitation>
). Spinnerets light brown (
<figureCitation id="13694CCEDC7F1A72970AB6B788ABA5E4" box="[341,429,1748,1775]" captionStart="Figs 58–63" captionStartId="25.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,613,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-70@25.[189,1398,610,1869]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 58–63. Physocyclus lyncis sp. nov. Female (holotype). 58–60. Habitus in dorsal, lateral and ventral views, respectively. 61–63. Epigynum in ventral, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. Scale bars: 58– 60 = 1 mm; 61–63 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484139/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED504BDC7F1A7296E2B7758B95A47C" blockId="26.[187,1399,1814,1911]" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">
EPIGYNUM. Wider than long, with semisquare shape in anterior part; VAE long, wide, semicircular distally and almost flat, pointing downwards (
<figureCitation id="13694CCEDC7F1A729424B75A8A01A45F" box="[635,775,1849,1876]" captionStart="Figs 58–63" captionStartId="25.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,613,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-70@25.[189,1398,610,1869]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 58–63. Physocyclus lyncis sp. nov. Female (holotype). 58–60. Habitus in dorsal, lateral and ventral views, respectively. 61–63. Epigynum in ventral, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. Scale bars: 58– 60 = 1 mm; 61–63 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484139/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Figs 61–62</figureCitation>
). Pale region close to epigastric furrow (
<figureCitation id="13694CCEDC7F1A7292B7B75A8C47A45F" box="[1256,1345,1849,1876]" captionStart="Figs 58–63" captionStartId="25.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,613,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-70@25.[189,1398,610,1869]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 58–63. Physocyclus lyncis sp. nov. Female (holotype). 58–60. Habitus in dorsal, lateral and ventral views, respectively. 61–63. Epigynum in ventral, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. Scale bars: 58– 60 = 1 mm; 61–63 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484139/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
). PP wide, sclerotized arc of uterus (
<figureCitation id="13694CCEDC7F1A729471B73F8B80A47C" box="[558,646,1884,1911]" captionStart="Figs 58–63" captionStartId="25.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,613,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-70@25.[189,1398,610,1869]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 58–63. Physocyclus lyncis sp. nov. Female (holotype). 58–60. Habitus in dorsal, lateral and ventral views, respectively. 61–63. Epigynum in ventral, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. Scale bars: 58– 60 = 1 mm; 61–63 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484139/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="199">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
